@jmtd my pleasure! Yes, these assets are derived from a vector (SVG) source, however PNG assets are still the best for icons due to technical shortcomings in librsvg.
I could make it look more like the original doom logo by making it two tones of "chocolate" or something like that in the way the original D has two tones.
My reasoning for dropping the ice cream cone was to simplify the metaphor; it is more likely to be interpreted as "ice cream doom" than "chocolate doom" with the cone in there. ;) Also, assets derived from photographs are usually not necessarily the best for icons, as they don't scale well.

